Executive Profile
Michael D. O'Halleran  Executive Chairman, Aon Benfield Global, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships67--
Background

		Mr. Michael D. O'Halleran, also known as Mike, serves as an Executive Chairman of Aon Benfield Inc., Aon Benfield Limited and Aon Benfield Global, Inc. Mr. O'Halleran serves as an Executive Chairman of Aon Benfield Group Limited and served as its Chairman. He served as Senior Executive Vice President of Aon plc since September 2004. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Aon Benfield Group Limited. He has more than 33 years of experience in the insurance and reinsurance ... industries. He founded Aon Re Global in 1987. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Hewlett Packard. He served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Aon Corporation from April 16, 1999 to September 30, 2004. He served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Aon Group Inc., a subsidiary of Aon Corporation from 1995 to September 30, 2004. He served in other significant senior management positions within AON group of companies since 1987. He served as a Senior Executive with well-known companies within the insurance industry, including Wausau Insurance Companies, General Reinsurance and Alexander Re. He serves as a Co-Chairman of World Business Chicago and Trustee of Dublin City University in Dublin, Ireland. He has been a Director of Allegiance Corporation since 1996 and NuVasive, Inc. since August 1, 2016. He serves as a Director at OptiMark US Equities, Inc. and World Business Chicago. He serves as a Trustee of Lake Forest College. He served as an Independent Director of CareFusion Corporation from 2009 to March 17, 2015. He served as a Director of Cardinal Health, Inc. from 1999 to 2009. He served as a Director of Aon Corporation and Cardinal Health 414, LLC since 1999. He served as a Director of Care Fusion, Inc. and Benfield Group Ltd. He is a Director of a number of charitable and educational organizations, including Providence-St. Mel High School and the Angus Robinson Jr. He is a Member of the Economic Club of Chicago and the World President Organization. Mr. O'Halleran has a degree in Accounting and Finance from the University of Wisconsin-Whitewater.Read Full Background




